        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;">Veg Briyani</h2>
        <img style="padding-left:225px;width:400px;height:400px" src="https://www.indianveggiedelight.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/veg-biryani-instant-pot.jpg" alt="Veg Briyani">
        <div id="en">
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Ingredients:</p>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px"> For Rice:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 1.5 cups Basmati rice</li>
                <li> Water for soaking and cooking rice</li>
                <li> 2-3 green cardamom pods</li>
                <li> 2-3 cloves</li>
                <li> 1-inch cinnamon stick</li>
                <li> 1 bay leaf</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">   For Vegetable Mix:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 2 cups mixed vegetables (carrots, peas, beans, potatoes, etc.), diced</li>
                <li> 1 large onion, thinly sliced and 2 tomatoes, chopped</li>
                <li> 2 green chilies, slit</li>
                <li> 2 tablespoons cooking oil or ghee (clarified butter) </li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon cumin seeds, 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
                <li> 1/2 cup yogurt</li>
                <li> 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder, 1 teaspoon red chili powder, 1 teaspoon garam masala powder</li>
                <li> 1/2 cup fresh coriander leaves,1/2 cup fresh mint leaves, chopped</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px">   For Garnish:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> Fried onions </li>
                <li> Saffron strands soaked in warm milk</li>
                <li> Ghee </li>

            </ul>
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Instructions:</p>
            <br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">1. Rinse and Soak Rice:</li><ul>
                <li> Wash the Basmati rice thoroughly under cold water until the water runs clear.</li>
                <li> Soak the rice in enough water for about 30 minutes. Drain and set aside.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">2. Cook the Rice:</li><ul>
                <li> In a large pot, bring water to boil.</li>
                <li> Add the soaked and drained rice, green cardamom pods, cloves, cinnamon stick, bay leaf, and salt.</li>
                <li> Cook the rice until it's 70-80% cooked (it should have a slight bite). Drain the rice and set it aside.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">3. Prepare Vegetable Mix:</li><ul>
                <li> In a large, heavy-bottomed pan or a biryani pot, heat oil or ghee over medium heat.</li>
                <li> Add cumin seeds and let them splutter. </li>
                <li> Add sliced onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.</li>
                <li> Add ginger-garlic paste and green chilies. Sauté for a couple of minutes until the raw smell disappears.</li>
                <li> Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and the oil starts to separate.</li>


            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">4. Add Spices:</li><ul>
                <li> Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, and garam masala powder. Mix well and cook for a few minutes.</li>


            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">5. Add Vegetables and Yogurt:</li><ul>
                <li> Add the diced mixed vegetables and sauté for a few minutes.</li>
                <li> Add yogurt and mix well. Cook until the vegetables are partially cooked.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">6. Layering:</li><ul>
                <li> In the same pan, layer the partially cooked rice over the vegetable mixture.</li>
                <li> Sprinkle chopped coriander leaves and mint leaves over the rice.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">7. Garnish:</li><ul>
                <li> Garnish with fried onions and saffron-soaked milk.</li>
                <li> Drizzle a little ghee (clarified butter) on top for added flavor.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">8. Dum Cooking:</li><ul>
                <li> Cover the pan with a tight-fitting lid or seal with aluminum foil.</li>
                <li> Cook on low heat (dum cooking) for about 20-25 minutes.</li>
                <li> This allows the flavors to meld, and the rice and vegetables to fully cook.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">9. Serve:</li><ul>
                <li> Gently fluff the Vegetable Biryani with a fork.</li>
                <li> Serve hot with raita (yogurt with spices), salad, or a side of your choice.</li>

            </ul><p style="color:orange;font-size:20px">  Enjoy your homemade Vegetable Biryani, a fragrant and flavorful Indian rice dish!</p>
